subsection.def:
animal carcasses (動物屍體) means the bodies of any
                                animals that are carried on board as cargo and that die or are
                                euthanized during the voyage;

cargo remnants (貨物剩餘物), in relation to a ship,
                                means the remnants of any cargo other than those which are regulated
                                under any other subsidiary legislation made under the Ordinance;

subparagraph.content:
the transport of harvested fish (including
                                                  shellfish) from the facility to shore for
                                                  processing;

subsection.def:
incinerator ashes (焚化爐灰燼) means ashes and clinkers
                                resulting from the incineration of garbage on board a ship or a
                                fixed or floating platform;

solid wastes (固體廢棄物) means all solid wastes
                                (including slurries) other than those which are regulated under any
                                other subsidiary legislation made under the Ordinance;

special cargo residues (特殊貨物殘餘物) means cargo residues
                                which cannot be recovered using commonly available methods for
                                unloading;

paragraph.content:
that is necessary for the purpose of securing the
                                                safety of the ship and the persons on board the ship
                                                or of saving life at sea;

subparagraph.content:
the details of the garbage discharged, including the categories of the
                        garbage and the estimated amount for each category in cubic
                        metres;
